==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Aghast
<hw>A*ghast"</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a. & p. p.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>agast</ets>, <ets>agasted</ets>, p. p. of <ets>agasten</ets> to
terrify, fr. AS. pref. <ets>⟦amac⟧-</ets> (cf. Goth. <ets>us-</ets>, G.
<ets>er-</ets>, orig. meaning <ets>out</ets>) + <ets>g⟦ae⟧stan</ets> to
terrify, torment: cf. Goth. <ets>usgaisjan</ets> to terrify, primitively
to fix, to root to the spot with terror; akin to L. <ets>haerere</ets>
to stick fast, cling. See <er>Gaze</er>, <er>Hesitate</er>.]</ety>
<def>Terrified; struck with amazement; showing signs of terror or
horror.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Aghast</qex> he waked; and, starting from his bed,⟦br⟧
Cold sweat in clammy drops his limbs o'erspread.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The commissioners read and stood <qex>aghast</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Macaulay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Agible</ent>⟦br⟧
